Applying Styles Directly to HTML Elements

You can apply styles directly to HTML elements using the style attribute. This attribute allows you to specify CSS properties and their values within the HTML element itself.

Example:

HTML
<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
    <title>Inline Styles Example</title>
</head>
<body>
    <h1 style="color: blue; font-size: 36px;">Hello, World!</h1>
    <p style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 18px;">This is a paragraph with inline styles.</p>
</body>
</html>

